                        <objectDesc>
                            <supportDesc>
                                <support><p>An ivory token carved on one long side in the form of  two clasped left hands, and cut vertically smooth on the reverse, on which face are four lines of Greek letters. A crack runs diagonally across the upper left corner of the reverse, and a fragment is lost from the upper edge of the middle of the rear (inscribed) face. Slight damage to the lower corners.</p>
